The paper proposes a new graph neural network architecture for graph classification, which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of convolutional networks and hierarchical structures suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of differentiable pooling and the importance of preserving graph information, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
